html:
141 U.S. 249

11 S.Ct. 1005

35 L.Ed. 628

WILLIAMS
v.
PASSUMPSIC SAV. BANK.

April 6, 1891.

H. Bisbee, for plaintiff in error.

Henry C. Ide, for defendant in error.

FULLER, C. J.

1

The mandate in this cause will issue forthwith, and if the plaintiff in error seasonably take and prosecute an appeal from that rendered by the circuit court, leave will be granted to file as part of the return on said appeal the transcript of the record in this cause.
